<br>
We make our own meaning.<br>
<br>
I CHOOSE  to value some things though. I have no problem mining an asteroid, or colonizing the moon. I CHOOSE not to interfere with wilderness on Earth. I CHOOSE not to damage people. There is no reason for these choices except that I have so chosen.<br>
<br>
That is what is hard for quite religious people to understand. Their choices come from what they interpret to be the absolute commands of an Absolute Authority. Can someone without an Anchor lead a just and wothy life. If WE make up the rules about right and wrong, do we not end up with a Charles Manson?<br>
<br>
