I don't know anybody who considers themselves to be atheist or agnostic who follows Nihilism (&quot;There's no Maker, no purpose. Life is and it sucks, so get your kicks while you can&quot;). If there is no absolute Judge in the sky, waiting to exact final revenge against sinners, then you can't just say that Hitler is dead, and the almighty Dog sits in judgement, so he's getting his due. There is no such thing (in the non-theistic world view).<br>
All a creep leaves behind is the bad memories he's left on others. Conversely, a good person hasn't gone on to a better place -but we're still not left only with despair &amp; the dust of the dead, because we make <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">memories</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->, and that makes us the most powerful thing in existence!<br>
